context.text:
 Alternative IEC-61000-3-2 requirements with respect to the input current [25] for those electronic ballasts with rated lamp power below 23 W are:

•
third harmonic less than 86% of the fundamental (prototype: 82%);

•
fifth harmonic less than 61% of the fundamental (prototype: 62%);

•
starting angle less than 60° (prototype: 49.2°);

•
ending angle greater than 90° (prototype: 93.5\${\circ}\$).

Mode locking of monolithic semiconductor lasers based on QDs offers several advantages [4], [8]:

•
broad gain spectrum, allowing for a theoretical minimum pulse width below 100 fs;

•
low temperature sensitivity of threshold current—high \${\rm T}_{0}\$;

•
low line width enhancement factor for Fourier limited pulses;

•
ultrafast gain/absorption recovery stages and low saturation energies for stable, wide range and low jitter mode locking;

•
suppressed lateral carrier diffusion, resulting in low beam filamentation and negligible side-wall carrier recombination for deep mesa devices.

